 BY AGNES NWORIE, ABAKALIKI Former Secretary to the Government of the Federation, Senator Anyim Pius Anyim, has felicitated with former President Olusegun Obasanjo on  his 85th birth anniversary. Anyim’s congratulatory message was contained in a statement made available to journalists in Abakaliki, the Ebonyi State capital. The statement described the celebrant as “a true citizen of the world, an outstanding leader in Africa and our nation’s pre-eminent statesman.” It read that the former president “demonstrated unwavering commitment to the unity, peace and progress of our dear country, Africa and the world at large. “I join your family, friends and associates all over the world, and indeed, all Nigerians to rejoice with you on this special occasion of your 85th birthday. “You stand out as a true patriot. You had continued to give your all to see that Nigeria takes her place among the comity of nations as a richly endowed country. “You had played key roles at various stages of Nigeria’s and Africa’s political history. At all those stages, you provided visionary and principled leadership guided by deep love for and commitment to the wellbeing of Nigerians and the black man. “You have remained a voice of reason, cautioning and proffering solutions as Nigeria wades through the many challenges of nation building. “You have written letters, books, given lectures at home and abroad, all in the effort to communicate your thoughts and ideas on how to make Nigeria work. As a result, your stature towers on the world stage. “Baba, I want to assure you that Nigerians appreciate you and your noble contributions to the peace, unity, progress and development of our dear country. “God has blessed you with good health, strength and sharp mind. May He continue to uphold you as you continue your worthy service to our dear country, Africa and the world at large. Happy Birthday Baba.” 